<div class="update-item">
    <div class="update-item__title">Transport Layer Improvements and Bug Fixes</div>
    <div class="update-item__description">
        Several transport-related PRs were merged, including fixes for WebRTC performance issues <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://github.com/libp2p/test-plans/pull/796">PR #796</a> and improvements to the transport interop runner <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://github.com/libp2p/test-plans/issues/789">this issue</a>.
    </div>
</div>

<div class="update-item">
    <div class="update-item__title">Swift-libp2p Security Fixes Merged</div>
    <div class="update-item__description">
        The swift-libp2p implementation received several security-related PRs, including fixes for input command sanitization <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://github.com/swift-libp2p/swift-libp2p/pull/42">PR #42</a> and redundant event loop handling <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://github.com/swift-libp2p/swift-libp2p/pull/44">PR #44</a>.
    </div>
</div>

<div class="update-item">
    <div class="update-item__title">Rust-libp2p WebTransport Support Added</div>
    <div class="update-item__description">
        The rust-libp2p implementation now supports WebTransport connections, enabling better browser compatibility. This was implemented in <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://github.com/libp2p/rust-libp2p/pull/1234">PR #1234</a> and follows the spec discussion in <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://github.com/libp2p/specs/issues/567">specs#567</a>.
    </div>
</div>

<div class="update-item">
    <div class="update-item__title">Python TLS Support Added to Test-Plans</div>
    <div class="update-item__description">
        The test-plans repository received a PR adding TLS support for Python, which was merged in <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://github.com/libp2p/test-plans/pull/798">PR #798</a>.
    </div>
</div>
